g.text: Conceptualization: Face of a millipede trapped in amber...
Authority: The lieutenant's command instantly lets all the wind out of your sails, like he overrode your mind or flicked some secret master-switch.
Kim Kitsuragi: "Shall we?" He looks ready to go.
You: "I'm fine, don't worry about it."
You: "There's nothing more to talk about, only to *endure*." [Leave.]
You: "It is a powerful metaphor, lieutenant. For my resolve."
You: "I'm sorry, Kim, I don't know what came over me."
Esprit de Corps: Should I contact his station's lazareth? Behind his back?
Kim Kitsuragi: "Are you fucking insane?!" the lieutenant snaps at you. "Don't answer that! And STOP doing it! Let's go."
You: "They say you can hear the ice crack from a..."
Kim Kitsuragi: "No, but you see, you don't," the lieutenant explains patiently, but his voice is very tired. "You are not Tequila Sunset and you are not an icebreaker. Stop, please!"
You: "I understand. It's not gonna become a thing."
Kim Kitsuragi: "No, but you see, you *don't*," the lieutenant explains patiently, although his voice is very tired suddenly. "You're not a firewalker, you're not an icebreaker."
You: "I don't need to 'move it', this is my final form."
Kim Kitsuragi: "Alright, detective," he reaches out and pats you on the arm. It feels strangely encouraging. "Let's get going, we've got a killer to catch."
Inland Empire: But somehow it doesn't scare him, like it scared you. Doesn't make him quiver with cold. Poor guy...
Volition: It's like he re-conditioned your brain.
Physical Instrument: That's a negative, lieutenant.
Kim Kitsuragi: "Oh, good." The lieutenant's posture relaxes. "Thank you! And sorry I asked about it. It's none of my business. Let's just get back to work."
Savoir Faire: The lieutenant is *not* loving the new look.
Kim Kitsuragi: "No, but you see, you don't," the lieutenant explains patiently, his voice suddenly tired. "You don't plough anything, you help me solve this case, please remember."
Suggestion: Better keep the lieutenant in the dark about the whole 'Icebreaker' thing. He's not gonna get it.
Kim Kitsuragi: "So now you want to go blind as well?" He shakes his head. "How about we become Those Who Solve Murder Cases instead and get back to work?"
Kim Kitsuragi: "I don't think *you* are supposed to call yourself that." A fleeting smile crosses his lips. "But I appreciate the honesty. Now let's get back to work."
Rhetoric: Neither was an actual question.
Kim Kitsuragi: "No, but you see, you don't," the lieutenant explains patiently, although his voice is suddenly very tired. "You're not an icebreaker or a firewalker, or even Tequila Sunset."
Savoir Faire: Suddenly the whole Icebreaker concept seems... just lame.
You: "This is what I am now, Kim. What I was always meant to be."
Kim Kitsuragi: "No, but you see, you don't," the lieutenant explains patiently, but his voice is very tired. "You're not an icebreaker, Harry. Please stop."
Kim Kitsuragi: "It's okay," he says quietly. "We're both under a lot of stress right now. Let's just try to not let it get to us and remember what we came here to do."
Kim Kitsuragi: "No, you are not. What you are is an RCM lieutenant conducting a murder investigation."
You: "I plough my way towards the frigid lands of Katla and Vaasa, smashing every ice sheet in my path..."
Kim Kitsuragi: "You don't look fine and I'm *very* worried about it." He crosses his arms on his chest.
Kim Kitsuragi: "No, you are not. What you are is an officer of the Revachol Citizens Militia conducting a murder investigation."

Kim Kitsuragi: "No, but you see, you don't," the lieutenant explains patiently, although his voice is suddenly very tired. "You're not an icebreaker or a firewalker, or even Raphaël Ambrosius Costeau."
Kim Kitsuragi: "What temptations is *He* withstanding then?" asks the lieutenant with a puzzled look.
Kim Kitsuragi: "You know what? I don't even want to know. Let it be one of your *internal* side-cases. I just want to get back to work."
Kim Kitsuragi: "Hm." The lieutenant seems almost impressed. "Admitting a problem is the first step forward. Perhaps now we can finally get some work done."
Kim Kitsuragi: "The last kingsman..." he repeats pensively, inspecting your face. "That's fitting, I suppose. Almost as if you *did* manage to turn back time. If only for yourself."
Kim Kitsuragi: "I just don't understand, officer." The lieutenant just stands there, looking perplexed. "Please, help me understand."
Kim Kitsuragi: "And what is that? A walking mask?"
Kim Kitsuragi: "Yes, your face." He nods, looking worried. "Looks like you're having a stroke. Can you even move it?"
Kim Kitsuragi: "No, but you see, you don't," the lieutenant explains patiently, but his voice is very tired. "You're not Raphaël Ambrosius Costeau and you're not an icebreaker!"
Kim Kitsuragi: "What happened to you?" the lieutenant asks as he leans in, eyes mapping your frozen face.
You: "Absolutely." (Lift the corners of your mouth with index fingers.) "See?"
Kim Kitsuragi: "You look... different. Constipated somehow?"
You: "He Who Stares Straight into the Eclipse."
Kim Kitsuragi: "No, but you see, you don't," the lieutenant explains patiently, but his voice is very tired. "Your name is Harrier Du Bois, not 'Icebreaker'."
Kim Kitsuragi: "Okay, that's all right." He looks visibly relieved. "As long as you understand it is a metaphor and don't build a persona around it."
